title: Autodesk Revit Beginner Tutorial - Video
description:
Autodesk Revit is building information modeling software for architects, structural engineers, MEP engineers, designers and 

contractors. It allows users to design a building and structure and its components in 3D, annotate the model with 2D 

drafting elements, and access building information from the building model's database. Revit is 4D BIM capable with tools to 

plan and track various stages in the building's lifecycle, from concept to construction and later demolition.

This Tutorial Absolutly for Beginers

includes:
Part 1 -- Basic Use
Part 2 -- Floor Plan
Part 3 -- Grid & Columns
Part 4 -- Stairs
Part 5 -- Annotation 
Part 6 -- Bringing At Together
Part 7 -- Rendering
